for more info visit<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>8) Kohn Swain<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With a wealth of experience and expertise in maritime law, Kohn Swain takes the No. 1 spot on our list of the top maritime attorneys in Houston. Not only does the firm handle individual cases, but it also provides services for business owners and other organizations. The wide range of service offerings, as well as a diverse client base, is a testament to the quality services provided by Kohn Swain.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7) Heninger Garrison Davis<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are considering hiring a maritime attorney, look no further than Heninger Garrison Davis. This law firm is regarded as one of the top law firms dealing with maritime matters and international trade, but they are also considered some of the best maritime attorneys in Houston.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>6) Windle Turley Martin &amp; Garrison<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Windle Turley has been practicing maritime law for nearly 40 years, representing both sides of the spectrum as an attorney and a captain. He earned his J.D. from the University of Texas School of Law before earning his M.S. degree at the University of Alabama\u2019s Nautical Science Program and receiving his Captains License from the United States Coast Guard Academy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>5) Moore Law Firm PLLC<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Moore Law Firm is a full-service maritime law firm based out of Houston, Texas. These are some of the top maritime attorneys you need to know in the area.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>4) Aleman, Brown &amp; Fernandez LLP<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The maritime attorneys at Aleman, Brown &amp; Fernandez LLP represent shipping and transportation companies with regard to their commercial operations. The firm is ranked among the top maritime law firms in the country.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3) Stewart R. Russell Attorney at Law<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Russell has over 26 years of experience practicing maritime law. He is well known for his representation of shipowners and underwriters involved in marine casualty litigation, including collisions, groundings, explosions and sinking. His practice also includes general commercial litigation, construction disputes and insurance coverage matters. He represents clients throughout the U.S., but mainly in Texas, Louisiana and Mississippi. Russell earned his bachelor\u2019s degree from the University of Texas at Austin before earning a juris doctorate from South Texas College of Law. He became a member of the State Bar of Texas in 1990 after passing the bar exam on his first attempt.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2) Sacks Tierney Watson, LLP<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sacks Tierney Watson, LLP is a maritime law firm based out of Houston and handles cases involving piracy, marine insurance, maritime law and other areas of maritime litigation. Its attorneys have been featured on CNN International, The New York Times and the Wall Street Journal. Sacks Tierney Watson has also worked with the United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime to help fight human trafficking across the globe. The firm\u2019s founder, Patrick J. Sacks, was named one of the top 100 lawyers in America by The National Law Journal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1) Crumpler Abbitt Solomons &amp; Laake, PC<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Crumpler Abbitt Solomons &amp; Laake is the go-to maritime attorney for business owners who live in the greater Houston area. The company offers a wide range of services for both commercial and personal interests, providing clients with financial advice, asset protection plans, corporate law assistance and more. The firm\u2019s reputation precedes it: the firm has been featured on a number of local news outlets, including the Houston Chronicle and KPRC 2 News. If you are looking for the best legal representation possible, contact the experts at Crumpler Abbitt Solomons &amp; Laake today!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you\u2019re a seafarer, chances are that you have at least once been involved in an accident or have had<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media"